Switch the Package Manager from YUM to DNF:
In CentOS 8, the default package manager yum has been replaced by the dnf (Dandified Yum).

Therefore, we have to switch to the dnf package manager before upgrading our CentOS 7 server.

Install dnf package manager using yum command.

[root@centos-7-server ~]# yum install -y dnf
